previous_version.title: AWS Lambda
previous_version.page_content: AWS Lambda is a compute service that lets you run code without provisioning or managing servers. It executes your code only when needed and scales automatically, from a few requests per day to thousands per second.# Best Practices- Write stateless functions: Ensure your Lambda functions are stateless to enable scaling.- Manage dependencies: Always declare and manage your dependencies explicitly in your deployment package.- Use environment variables: Store configuration in environment variables rather than in your function code.- Monitor and log: Use Amazon CloudWatch to log and monitor your Lambda functions.# Code ExamplesExample of a simple AWS Lambda function in Python:```pythonimport jsondef lambda_handler(event, context):    # TODO implement    return {        'statusCode': 200,        'body': json.dumps('Hello from Lambda!')    }```This function returns a simple greeting when invoked. Make sure to include error handling and logging in your real-world applications.
